modules.description: Provides functions to interact with browser extension APIs, including managing background scripts, handling message passing, and manipulating tabs. Works with data types such as JSON values, tab identifiers, and event listeners. Enables creation of browser extensions that communicate between components and modify web page behavior.

Provides functions to interact with browser local storage, including retrieving and setting items by key, fetching multiple items by list of keys, and clearing storage. Works with strings, lists of strings, and JavaScript objects wrapped in Js_of_ocaml types. Used to persist user preferences, cache data temporarily, and synchronize state between sessions.
